ANTHRAX - ZAMBIA (05): (WESTERN PROVINCE) FATALITIES
****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 7 Feb 2017
Source: ZNBC [edited]
http://www.znbc.co.zm/?p=48765


To date, 6 people have died of anthrax in Lulangu'nyi Ward in Chief Namulimbwa' s area in Sikongo District in Western Province, and 2 other people are admitted in Kalabo District hospital.

Sikongo Health Director Fredrick Siyunda and Lulangu'nyi Ward Councilor Kennedy Simbotwe have both confirmed the development to ZANIS [Zambia News and Information Services] in Kalabo in separate interviews.

Counselor Simbotwe disclosed that the 6 people died in a space of 5 days with the latest death recorded today [7 Feb 2017]. He said out of the 6, 2 were men while 4 were women. Dr Siyunda said his ministry has also engaged the department of livestock to ensure people are treated and animals get vaccinated. He said community members were allegedly hiding meat from sick animals in their homes each time health officers were on the ground to help dispose of the carcasses.

Dr Siyunda has since appealed to community members in affected areas to stop eating meat from dead animals if the disease is to be contained.

