[Ongoing human cases and deaths would suggest that bovine cases are still occurring, possibly in new areas outside direct veterinary oversight. Apropos, latterly there have been a number of Zambian news reports on this epidemic but none added anything new, just journalistic cut-and-paste, which to a cynical outsider, suggests that the journalists are getting rural gossip from their contacts and relatives but no editorial permission to go scouting out possible new areas and stories. "It's just anthrax. They get it all the time out there." Maybe, but one of the proven ways to stop human cases is to radically sharpen human awareness of the risks, and to make sure that the livestock in the various areas get vaccinated without delay.

The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=22476 or in ProMED 20170124.4787317. - Mod.MHJ]
